{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm a medical illustrator,"},{"time":3000,"text":"and I come from a slightly different point of view."},{"time":6000,"text":"I've been watching, since I grew up,"},{"time":9000,"text":"the expressions of truth and beauty in the arts"},{"time":13000,"text":"and truth and beauty in the sciences."},{"time":15000,"text":"And while these are both wonderful things in their own right --"},{"time":18000,"text":"they both have very wonderful things going for them --"},{"time":21000,"text":"truth and beauty as ideals that can be looked at by the sciences"},{"time":27000,"text":"and by math are almost like the ideal conjoined twins"},{"time":32000,"text":"that a scientist would want to date."},{"time":35000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":37000,"text":"These are expressions of truth as awe-full things,"},{"time":42000,"text":"by meaning they are things you can worship."},{"time":45000,"text":"They are ideals that are powerful. They are irreducible."},{"time":50000,"text":"They are unique. They are useful --"},{"time":52000,"text":"sometimes, often a long time after the fact."},{"time":55000,"text":"And you can actually roll some of the pictures now,"},{"time":57000,"text":"because I don't want to look at me on the screen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61000,"text":"Truth and beauty are things"},{"time":63000,"text":"that are often opaque to people who are not in the sciences."},{"time":68000,"text":"They are things that describe beauty in a way"},{"time":74000,"text":"that is often only accessible if you understand the language"},{"time":79000,"text":"and the syntax of the person"},{"time":81000,"text":"who studies the subject in which truth and beauty is expressed."},{"time":84000,"text":"If you look at the math, E=mc squared,"},{"time":87000,"text":"if you look at the cosmological constant,"},{"time":90000,"text":"where there's an anthropic ideal, where you see that life had to evolve"},{"time":95000,"text":"from the numbers that describe the universe --"},{"time":98000,"text":"these are things that are really difficult to understand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101000,"text":"And what I've tried to do"},{"time":102000,"text":"since I had my training as a medical illustrator --"},{"time":104000,"text":"since I was taught animation by my father,"},{"time":107000,"text":"who was a sculptor and my visual mentor --"},{"time":111000,"text":"I wanted to figure out a way to help people"},{"time":115000,"text":"understand truth and beauty in the biological sciences"},{"time":119000,"text":"by using animation, by using pictures, by telling stories"},{"time":123000,"text":"so that the things that are not necessarily evident to people"},{"time":127000,"text":"can be brought forth, and can be taught, and can be understood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":131000,"text":"Students today are often immersed in an environment"},{"time":137000,"text":"where what they learn is subjects that have truth and beauty"},{"time":142000,"text":"embedded in them, but the way they're taught is compartmentalized"},{"time":147000,"text":"and it's drawn down to the point where the truth and beauty"},{"time":152000,"text":"are not always evident."},{"time":153000,"text":"It's almost like that old recipe for chicken soup"},{"time":156000,"text":"where you boil the chicken until the flavor is just gone."},{"time":161000,"text":"We don't want to do that to our students."},{"time":163000,"text":"So we have an opportunity to really open up education."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167000,"text":"And I had a telephone call from Robert Lue at Harvard,"},{"time":170000,"text":"in the Molecular and Cellular Biology Department,"},{"time":172000,"text":"a couple of years ago. He asked me if my team and I"},{"time":176000,"text":"would be interested and willing to really change"},{"time":180000,"text":"how medical and scientific education is done at Harvard."},{"time":183000,"text":"So we embarked on a project that would explore the cell --"},{"time":188000,"text":"that would explore the truth and beauty inherent"},{"time":191000,"text":"in molecular and cellular biology"},{"time":193000,"text":"so that students could understand a larger picture"},{"time":196000,"text":"that they could hang all of these facts on."},{"time":199000,"text":"They could have a mental image of the cell"},{"time":202000,"text":"as a large, bustling, hugely complicated city"},{"time":210000,"text":"that's occupied by micro-machines."}]},{"cues":[{"time":212000,"text":"And these micro-machines really are at the heart of life."},{"time":215000,"text":"These micro-machines,"},{"time":216000,"text":"which are the envy of nanotechnologists the world over,"},{"time":220000,"text":"are self-directed, powerful, precise, accurate devices"},{"time":227000,"text":"that are made out of strings of amino acids."},{"time":230000,"text":"And these micro-machines power how a cell moves."},{"time":234000,"text":"They power how a cell replicates. They power our hearts."},{"time":239000,"text":"They power our minds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241000,"text":"And so what we wanted to do was to figure out"},{"time":245000,"text":"how we could make this story into an animation"},{"time":248000,"text":"that would be the centerpiece of BioVisions at Harvard,"},{"time":252000,"text":"which is a website that Harvard has"},{"time":256000,"text":"for its molecular and cellular biology students"},{"time":258000,"text":"that will -- in addition to all the textual information,"},{"time":263000,"text":"in addition to all the didactic stuff --"},{"time":265000,"text":"put everything together visually, so that these students"},{"time":268000,"text":"would have an internalized view of what a cell really is"},{"time":272000,"text":"in all of its truth and beauty, and be able to study"},{"time":276000,"text":"with this view in mind, so that their imaginations would be sparked,"},{"time":280000,"text":"so that their passions would be sparked"},{"time":283000,"text":"and so that they would be able to go on"},{"time":285000,"text":"and use these visions in their head to make new discoveries"},{"time":289000,"text":"and to be able to find out, really, how life works."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292000,"text":"So we set out by looking at how these molecules are put together."},{"time":299000,"text":"We worked with a theme, which is, you've got macrophages"},{"time":305000,"text":"that are streaming down a capillary,"},{"time":307000,"text":"and they're touching the surface of the capillary wall,"},{"time":310000,"text":"and they're picking up information from cells"},{"time":312000,"text":"that are on the capillary wall, and they are given this information"},{"time":316000,"text":"that there's an inflammation somewhere outside,"},{"time":319000,"text":"where they can't see and sense."},{"time":321000,"text":"But they get the information that causes them to stop,"},{"time":324000,"text":"causes them to internalize that they need to make"},{"time":328000,"text":"all of the various parts that will cause them to change their shape,"},{"time":333000,"text":"and try to get out of this capillary and find out what's going on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":338000,"text":"So these molecular motors -- we had to work"},{"time":340000,"text":"with the Harvard scientists and databank models"},{"time":346000,"text":"of the atomically accurate molecules"},{"time":349000,"text":"and figure out how they moved, and figure out what they did."},{"time":353000,"text":"And figure out how to do this in a way"},{"time":355000,"text":"that was truthful in that it imparted what was going on,"},{"time":361000,"text":"but not so truthful that the compact crowding in a cell"},{"time":366000,"text":"would prevent the vista from happening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":369000,"text":"And so what I'm going to show you is a three-minute"},{"time":373000,"text":"Reader's Digest version of the first aspect of this film"},{"time":376000,"text":"that we produced. It's an ongoing project"},{"time":379000,"text":"that's going to go another four or five years."},{"time":382000,"text":"And I want you to look at this"},{"time":384000,"text":"and see the paths that the cell manufactures --"},{"time":388000,"text":"these little walking machines, they're called kinesins --"},{"time":392000,"text":"that take these huge loads"},{"time":394000,"text":"that would challenge an ant in relative size."},{"time":397000,"text":"Run the movie, please."}]},{"cues":[{"time":401000,"text":"But these machines that power the inside of the cells"},{"time":404000,"text":"are really quite amazing, and they really are the basis of all life"},{"time":408000,"text":"because all of these machines interact with each other."},{"time":413000,"text":"They pass information to each other."},{"time":415000,"text":"They cause different things to happen inside the cell."},{"time":418000,"text":"And the cell will actually manufacture the parts that it needs"},{"time":421000,"text":"on the fly, from information"},{"time":423000,"text":"that's brought from the nucleus by molecules that read the genes."},{"time":428000,"text":"No life, from the smallest life to everybody here,"},{"time":433000,"text":"would be possible without these little micro-machines."},{"time":436000,"text":"In fact, it would really, in the absence of these machines,"},{"time":440000,"text":"have made the attendance here, Chris, really quite sparse."},{"time":442000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":446000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":458000,"text":"This is the FedEx delivery guy of the cell."},{"time":462000,"text":"This little guy is called the kinesin,"},{"time":464000,"text":"and he pulls a sack that's full of brand new manufactured proteins"},{"time":468000,"text":"to wherever it's needed in the cell --"},{"time":470000,"text":"whether it's to a membrane, whether it's to an organelle,"},{"time":473000,"text":"whether it's to build something or repair something."},{"time":475000,"text":"And each of us has about 100,000 of these things"},{"time":479000,"text":"running around, right now,"},{"time":481000,"text":"inside each one of your 100 trillion cells."},{"time":484000,"text":"So no matter how lazy you feel,"},{"time":487000,"text":"you're not really intrinsically doing nothing."},{"time":489000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":493000,"text":"So what I want you to do when you go home"},{"time":495000,"text":"is think about this, and think about how powerful our cells are."},{"time":499000,"text":"And think about some of the things"},{"time":500000,"text":"that we're learning about cellular mechanics."},{"time":504000,"text":"Once we figure out all that's going on --"},{"time":507000,"text":"and believe me, we know almost a percent of what's going on --"},{"time":511000,"text":"once we figure out what's going on,"},{"time":512000,"text":"we're really going to be able to have a lot of control"},{"time":515000,"text":"over what we do with our health,"},{"time":517000,"text":"with what we do with future generations,"},{"time":520000,"text":"and how long we're going to live."},{"time":522000,"text":"And hopefully we'll be able to use this"},{"time":524000,"text":"to discover more truth, and more beauty."},{"time":527000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":541000,"text":"But it's really quite amazing that these cells, these micro-machines,"},{"time":546000,"text":"are aware enough of what the cell needs that they do their bidding."},{"time":551000,"text":"They work together. They make the cell do what it needs to do."},{"time":555000,"text":"And their working together helps our bodies --"},{"time":561000,"text":"huge entities that they will never see -- function properly."},{"time":566000,"text":"Enjoy the rest of the show. Thank you."},{"time":567000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}